    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s] </strong>in half lengthways, then wash to remove any grit from between the leaves</p><p>Top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>dill</strong> and <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanakopita-style-herby-gnocchi/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leeks</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanakopita-style-herby-gnocchi/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>gnocchi</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until beginning to crisp</p><p>Tip: Don't stir too often as this will prevent the gnocchi from crisping!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanakopita-style-herby-gnocchi/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under the cold tap until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze the water out of the spinach as much as you can then chop it roughly</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanakopita-style-herby-gnocchi/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min</p><p>Roll your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut into quarters</p><p>Combine the juice of 1/4 of your <strong>lemon[s]</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>lemon dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanakopita-style-herby-gnocchi/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze the juice of 1/4 of your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> into the pan and add <strong>most </strong>of the <strong>chopped dill </strong>and<strong> basil</strong> (save some for garnish!)</p><p>Season with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanakopita-style-herby-gnocchi/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crumble your<strong> Greek cheese</strong> into the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until the cheese starts to melt into the mixture</p><p>Transfer the <strong>crispy gnocchi </strong>to the pan and stir everything together \u2013 this is your <strong>spanakopita-style gnocchi</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spanakopita-style-herby-gnocchi/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spanakopita-style gnocchi </strong>with your<strong> salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>lemon dressing</strong> and season with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved chopped herbs </strong>and <strong>lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
